-- E-Star Alternativ Jumps a Third Day as Earnings Improve in March
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-16T09:48:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/e-star-alternativ-jumps-a-third-day-as-earnings-improve-in-march.html
E-Star Alternativ Nyrt. (ESTAR) , a
Hungarian energy company, gained for a third day after reporting
that earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and
amortization rose in March.  The shares rose 3.9 percent to 2,680 forint by 11:37 a.m.
in Budapest, after sinking to 2,500 forint, the lowest since May
2009, on April 11. Ebitda came in at 1.435 million euros ($1.87
million) last month, a 12 percent increase from February, the
company said in a  statement  to the Budapest Stock Exchange
today.  “We are a bit positively surprised with the March
results,” Peter Szentirmai, a Budapest-based analyst at  KBC
Groep NV (KBC) ’s broker unit, wrote in a research report, citing the
increase in Ebitda.  To contact the reporter on this story:
